KW  - Arbitrage pricing
KW  - Bond pricing
KW  - Term structure
KW  - Tax clientele
KW  - Tax option
AB  - In markets with taxes the deviations of the price of a bond from its present value may be due to tax clientele and tax option effects. Detecting these effects is complicated by noise in bond prices. Previous empirical research has lacked a theory of how tax effects will influence the deviations in the presence of noise. This paper develops such a theory and demonstrates a methodology for detecting tax effects. In empirical tests the tax option effect comes through most clearly, but the existence of tax clienteles cannot be ruled out.
